  "chapter": {
    "number": 15,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Eliphaz: Job Does Not Fear God"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Then Eliphaz the Temanite replied:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Does a wise man answer with empty counsel",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or fill his belly with the hot east wind?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Should he argue with useless words",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or speeches that serve no purpose?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But you even undermine the fear of God",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and hinder meditation before Him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For your iniquity instructs your mouth,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and you choose the language of the crafty.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your own mouth, not mine, condemns you;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your own lips testify against you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Were you the first man ever born?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Were you brought forth before the hills?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do you listen in on the council of God",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or limit wisdom to yourself?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What do you know that we do not?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "What do you understand that is not clear to us?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Both the gray-haired and the aged are on our side—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "men much older than your father.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Are the consolations of God not enough for you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "even words spoken gently to you?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why has your heart carried you away,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and why do your eyes flash,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3170
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "as you turn your spirit against God",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and pour such words from your mouth?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What is man, that he should be pure,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or one born of woman, that he should be righteous?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If God puts no trust in His holy ones,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "if even the heavens are not pure in His eyes,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "how much less man, who is vile and corrupt,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who drinks injustice like water?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Listen to me and I will inform you.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will describe what I have seen,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "what was declared by wise men",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and was not concealed from their fathers,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "to whom alone the land was given",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when no foreigner passed among them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A wicked man writhes in pain all his days;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "only a few years are reserved for the ruthless.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Sounds of terror fill his ears;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in his prosperity the destroyer attacks him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He despairs of his return from darkness;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he is marked for the sword.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He wanders about as food for vultures;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he knows the day of darkness is at hand.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Distress and anguish terrify him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "overwhelming him like a king poised to attack.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For he has stretched out his hand against God",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and has vaunted himself against the Almighty,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "rushing headlong at Him",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with a thick, studded shield.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though his face is covered with fat",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and his waistline bulges with flesh,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "he will dwell in ruined cities,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in abandoned houses destined to become rubble.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He will no longer be rich; his wealth will not endure.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "His possessions will not overspread the land.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 30,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He will not escape from the darkness;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the flame will wither his shoots,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and the breath of God’s mouth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will carry him away.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 31,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Let him not deceive himself with trust in emptiness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for emptiness will be his reward.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 32,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It will be paid in full before his time,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and his branch will not flourish.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 33,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He will be like a vine stripped of its unripe grapes,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like an olive tree that sheds its blossoms.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 34,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the company of the godless will be barren,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and fire will consume the tents of bribery.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 35,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They conceive trouble and give birth to evil;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "their womb is pregnant with deceit.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
